course_title: Women's Health Nurse Practitioner I - Reproductive Health Care for Women
course_description: Students will gain the knowledge/skills to differentiate abnormal from normal findings using advanced assessment techniques and critical thinking to formulate a diagnosis and plan of care as it pertains to the reproductive health care of culturally diverse patients.
prerequisites: NRSG 544 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
